<h2 id="getting-data-from-internet">Getting data from internet</h2>

<h4 id="web-scraping">Web scraping</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Data scraping used for extracting data from websites</li>
  <li>Its is not the most robust way to get data (website might change, legal issues)</li>
  <li>Anyway sometimes this is the only way to get the data</li>
  <li>Beyond the scope of this course, you will have lessons later in the program</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="data-through-apis">Data through APIs</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Right way to offer data</li>
  <li>Instead of a webpage, server returns a flat file in various formats (csv, json etc)</li>
  <li>Simplest way is REST</li>
  <li>Sometimes is password protected</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="obtaining-eurostat-data-through-api">Obtaining Eurostat data through API</h2>
<p>https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/web/main/data/database</p>

